<dl id="n10076b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10076b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10076b"> 76(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> on arrow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Artabaze, assi&eacute;geant la ville de Potid&eacute;e, y avait gagn&eacute; un certain Timox&egrave;ne, et communiquait avec lui au moyen de <mark>fl&egrave;ches</mark> lanc&eacute;es dans un lieu convenu, et auxquelles des lettres &eacute;taient attach&eacute;es. <font color="green">[Artabasus, during the siege of the city of Potidus, won over a certain Timoxenes as an ally there and communicated with him by means of arrows with letters attached to them that were shot to an agreed-upon location.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 23</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
